  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of international, national, and regulatory measures designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here's an overview:\n\n1. International Legal Framework:\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legal Components:\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n\n3. Key Regulatory Elements:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- International cooperation and information sharing\n\n5. Compliance Obligations:\n- Financial institutions\n- Casinos\n- Real estate professionals\n- Lawyers and accountants\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n\nThe framework aims to detect and prevent illicit financial activities through comprehensive legal and regulatory strategies.",
